name: Target.TargetType
desc: The different types of a target.

items.name: case regular
items.desc: A target that contains code for the Swift package’s functionality.

items.name: case binary
items.desc: A target that references a binary artifact.

items.name: case system
items.desc: A target that adapts a library on the system to work with Swift packages.

items.name: case test
items.desc: A target that contains tests for the Swift package’s other targets.

items.name: init?(rawValue: String)
items.desc: Creates a new instance with the specified raw value.

items.name: func encode(to: Encoder)
items.desc: Encodes this value into the given encoder, when the type’s RawValue is String.

items.name: func hash(into: inout Hasher)
items.desc: Hashes the target type by feeding the item into the given hasher.

items.name: static func != (Target.TargetType, Target.TargetType) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two values are not equal.

items.name: var rawValue: String
items.desc: The corresponding value of the raw type.

items.name: typealias Target.TargetType.RawValue
items.desc: The raw type that can be used to represent all values of the conforming type.
